- 'established carmaker' refers to Toyota;
- 'last decade' corresponds to the production years from 2010 to 2020;
- 'fuel efficiency' includes city, highway, and overall (combined) MPG.

- "thoroughbreds" refers to high-performance vehicles;
- "golden year" metaphorically signifies a notable or celebrated year in the automobile industry, in this case, 1985;
- "race towards fuel efficiency" metaphorically indicates competition for higher fuel efficiency;
- "breathing a bit easier on the planet" symbolizes lower environmental impact through lower emissions and better fuel efficiency.
